ngs that are over a century old in all the schools in the state would soon be demolished to give way for new ones. “Only just few days ago, Dr Fayemi promised to make life more comfortable for judicial officers in government employment, while Judges are assured of new set of vehicles. Female Judges too are to be promoted to the bench for the state judiciary to be gender sensitive. “According to report, the last time government purchased vehicles for Judges was during the first term of His Excellency. “This will in no small way improve the image of the Judges and enhance effective performance of their duties.” Elder Oluwalana, who doubles as the Senior Special Assistant on Media(Party Matters) to the state Governor, appealed to people of the state that what the administration requires at present is their maximum cooperation so that the ongoing developmental trend will be extended to other sectors of the economy. Vanguard News Nigeria The Ekiti State chapter of the Peoples Democratic Party (PDP), yesterday, blamed the opposition All Progressives Congress (APC) over the delay in the execution of the airport project in the state, saying the APC was only ashamed that a PDP government led by Governor Ayodele Fayose was showing the political… September 27, 2015 In "News" Describes his death as monumental loss By Rotimi Ojomoyela - Ado-Ekiti The Governor of Ekiti State, Dr. Kayode Fayemi, has described the Publisher of LEADERSHIP Newspapers, Mr Sam Nda-Isaiah's death as a monumental loss to the country in general, the media industry in particular, and the All Progressives Congress (APC),… December 12, 2020 In "News" Ado Ekiti—The Governor of Ekiti State, Mr Ayodele Fayose yesterday described his performance in the last one year, as satisfactory. October 14, 2015 In "News"